# Grimoire footprint reduction (#78 / v3.8) — suppress framework-internal
# artifacts from GitHub language stats and source archives WITHOUT moving them.
#
# - `linguist-documentation` keeps a file out of the repo's language bar and
#   marks it as documentation (it stays browsable; nothing is hidden from git).
# - `export-ignore` excludes a file from `git archive` tarballs (release
#   downloads) — appropriate for agent-only operational artifacts.
#
# These rules move nothing on disk, so they have ZERO impact on
# `sync-from-upstream`'s 3-way merge, the golden baseline, or bootstrap restore.
# Relocations (e.g. the path-locked `release-planning-v*.md`) are tracked
# separately in docs/design/footprint-reduction-design.md as migration-required.

# Accretive per-release operational artifacts (one file per release, forever).
docs/release-planning-*.md          linguist-documentation export-ignore
docs/qa-ledger.md                   linguist-documentation export-ignore

# Framework operational docs (agent-facing; project-facing-ish kept browsable).
docs/version-history.md             linguist-documentation
docs/roadmap.md                     linguist-documentation
docs/integration-workflow.md        linguist-documentation export-ignore
docs/version-design.md              linguist-documentation export-ignore

# Agent-only internal tier (the v1.17 docs/grimoire/ reorg) + research spikes.
docs/grimoire/**                    linguist-documentation export-ignore
docs/token-efficiency-*.md          linguist-documentation export-ignore
docs/execution-profile-spike-s1.md  linguist-documentation export-ignore

# Generated bytecode (already gitignored; mark in case a fork commits it).
**/__pycache__/**                   linguist-generated
*.pyc                               linguist-generated
